column1078: ['Because of _______s virulent poison and daunting physical prowess, no other species could hope to best it on the frozen highlands. Preferring solitude, this species does not form packs.']
column1079: ['Its lancelike spikes and savage temperament have earned it the nickname sea fiend. It slurps up poison to nourish itself.']
column1080: ['When it flies to this land from across the sea, the bitter winter comes to an end. According to legend, this Pokmons love gives rise to the budding of fresh life across Hisui.']
column1081: ['When it flies to this land from across the sea, the bitter winter comes to an end. According to legend, this Pokmons love gives rise to the budding of fresh life across Hisui.']
column1082: ['Its fluffy fur is similar in composition to plants. This Pokmon frequently washes its face to keep it from drying out.', 'The sweet scent its body gives off mesmerizes those around it. The scent grows stronger when this Pokmon is in the sun.']
column1083: ['_______ deftly wields the vine hidden beneath its long fur, slamming the hard flower bud against its opponents.', 'The hardness of _______s fur depends on the Pokmons mood. When _______ is prepared to battle, its fur becomes pointed and needle sharp.']
column1084: ['This Pokmon uses the reflective fur lining its cape to camouflage the stem of its flower, creating the illusion that the flower is floating.', 'With skillful misdirection, it rigs foes with pollen-packed flower bombs. _______ sets off the bombs before its foes realize whats going on.']
column1085: ['It lies on warm rocks and uses the heat absorbed by its square-shaped scales to create fire energy.', 'Its flame sac is small, so energy is always leaking out. This energy is released from the dent atop _______s head and flickers to and fro.']
column1086: ['The combination of _______s fire energy and overflowing vitality has caused an egg-shaped fireball to appear on the Pokmons head.', 'The valve in _______s flame sac is closely connected to its vocal cords. This Pokmon utters a guttural cry as it spews flames every which way.']
column1087: ['The fiery bird changes shape when _______ sings. Rumor has it that the bird was born when the fireball on _______s head gained a soul.', '_______s gentle singing soothes the souls of all that hear it. It burns its enemies to a crisp with flames of over 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit.']
column1088: ['This Pokmon migrated to Paldea from distant lands long ago. The gel secreted by its feathers repels water and grime.', 'Its strong legs let it easily swim around in even fast-flowing rivers. It likes to keep things tidy and is prone to overthinking things.']
column1089: ['These Pokmon constantly run through shallow waters to train their legs, then compete with each other to see which of them kicks most gracefully.', 'The hardworking _______ observes people and Pokmon from various regions and incorporates their movements into its own dance routines.']
column1090: ['A single kick from a _______ can send a truck rolling. This Pokmon uses its powerful legs to perform striking dances from far-off lands.', 'Dancing in ways that evoke far-away places, this Pokmon mesmerizes all that see it. Flourishes of its decorative water feathers slice into its foes.']
column1091: ['It searches for food all day. It possesses a keen sense of smell but doesnt use it for anything other than foraging.', 'This Pokmon spurns all but the finest of foods. Its body gives off an herblike scent that bug Pokmon detest.']
column1092: ['Oinkologne is proud of its fine, glossy skin. It emits a concentrated scent from the tip of its tail.', 'It entrances fe_______ Pokmon with the sweet, alluring scent that wafts from all over its body.']
column1093: ['Oinkologne is proud of its fine, glossy skin. It emits a concentrated scent from the tip of its tail.', 'It entrances _______ Pokmon with the sweet, alluring scent that wafts from all over its body.']
column1094: ['The ball of threads wrapped around its body is elastic enough to deflect the scythes of Scyther, this Pokmons natural enemy.', 'The thread it secretes from its rear is as strong as wire. The secret behind the threads strength is the topic of ongoing research.']
column1095: ['It clings to branches and ceilings using its threads and moves without a sound. It takes out its prey before the prey even notices it.', '_______ covers its territory in tough, sticky threads to set up traps for intruders.']
column1096: ['It has its third set of legs folded up. When its in a tough spot, this Pokmon jumps over 30 feet using the strength of its legs.', 'Its highly skilled at a fighting style in which it uses its jumping capabilities to dodge incoming attacks while also dealing damage to opponents.']
column1097: ['When it decides to fight all out, it stands on its previously folded legs to enter Showdown Mode. It neutralizes its enemies in short order.', 'It uses its normally folded third set of legs when in Showdown Mode. This places a huge burden on its body, so it cant stay in this mode for long.']
column1098: ['It has underdeveloped electric sacs on its cheeks. These sacs can produce electricity only if _______ rubs them furiously with the pads on its forepaws.', 'The pads of its paws are electricity-discharging organs. _______ fires electricity from its forepaws while standing unsteadily on its hind legs.']
column1099: ['When its group is attacked, _______ is the first to leap into battle, defeating enemies with a fighting technique that utilizes electric shocks.', '_______ uses a unique fighting technique in which it uses its forepaws to strike foes and zap them with electricity from its paw pads simultaneously.']
column1100: ['This Pokmon normally is slow to react, but once it enters battle, it will strike down its enemies with lightning-fast movements.', '_______s fluffy fur acts as a battery. It can store the same amount of electricity as an electric car.']
column1101: ['Exhibiting great teamwork, they use their incisors to cut pieces out of any material that might be useful for a nest, then make off with them.', 'The pair sticks together no matter what. They split any food they find exactly in half and then eat it together.']
column1102: ['The two little ones just appeared one day. The group might be a family of related Pokmon, but nobody knows for sure.', 'The larger pair protects the little ones during battles. When facing strong opponents, the whole group will join the fight.']
column1103: ['The two little ones just appeared one day. The group might be a family of related Pokmon, but nobody knows for sure.', 'The larger pair protects the little ones during battles. When facing strong opponents, the whole group will join the fight.']
column1104: ['This Pokmon is smooth and moist to the touch. Yeast in _______s breath induces fermentation in the Pokmons vicinity.', 'The yeast in _______s breath is useful for cooking, so this Pokmon has been protected by people since long ago.']
column1106: ['It protects itself from enemies by emitting oil from the fruit on its head. This oil is bitter and astringent enough to make someone flinch.', 'This Pokmon converts nutrients into oil, which it stores in the fruit on its head. It can easily go a whole week without eating or drinking.']
column1107: ['_______ shares its tasty, fresh-scented oil with others. This species has coexisted with humans since times long gone.', 'It basks in the sun to its hearts content until the fruits on its head ripen. After that, _______ departs from human settlements and goes on a journey.']
column1108: ['This calm Pokmon is very compassionate. It will share its delicious, nutrient-rich oil with weakened Pokmon.', 'This Pokmon drives back enemies by launching its rich, aromatic oil at them with enough force to smash a boulder.']
column1109: ['These Pokmon prefer to live in cities. They form flocks based on the color of their feathers, and they fight over territory.', 'Green-feathered flocks hold the most sway. When theyre out searching for food in the mornings and evenings, it gets very noisy.']
column1110: ['These Pokmon prefer to live in cities. They form flocks based on the color of their feathers, and they fight over territory.', 'Green-feathered flocks hold the most sway. When theyre out searching for food in the mornings and evenings, it gets very noisy.']
column1111: ['These Pokmon prefer to live in cities. They form flocks based on the color of their feathers, and they fight over territory.', 'Green-feathered flocks hold the most sway. When theyre out searching for food in the mornings and evenings, it gets very noisy.']
column1112: ['These Pokmon prefer to live in cities. They form flocks based on the color of their feathers, and they fight over territory.', 'Green-feathered flocks hold the most sway. When theyre out searching for food in the mornings and evenings, it gets very noisy.']
column1113: ['It was born in a layer of rock salt deep under the earth. This species was particularly treasured in the old days, as they would share precious salt.', 'The ground scrapes its body as it travels, causing it to leave salt behind. Salt is constantly being created and replenished inside _______s body.']
column1114: ['This Pokmon dry cures its prey by spraying salt over them. The curing process steals away the water in the preys body.', 'It compresses rock salt inside its body and shoots out hardened salt pellets with enough force to perforate an iron sheet.']
column1115: ['_______ will rub its fingertips together and sprinkle injured Pokmon with salt. Even severe wounds will promptly heal afterward.', 'Many Pokmon gather around _______, hoping to lick at its mineral-rich salt.']
column1119: ['_______ shakes its tail to generate electricity. If it senses danger, it will make its head blink on and off to alert its allies.', 'It floats using the electricity stored in its body. When thunderclouds are around, _______ will float higher off the ground.']
column1120: ['When this Pokmon expands and contracts its wobbly body, the belly-button dynamo in its stomach produces a huge amount of electricity.', 'What appear to be eyeballs are actually organs for discharging the electricity generated by _______s belly-button dynamo.']
column1121: ['When its wings catch the wind, the bones within produce electricity. This Pokmon dives into the ocean, catching prey by electrocuting them.', 'These Pokmon make their nests on coastal cliffs. The nests have a strange, crackling texture, and theyre a popular delicacy.']
column1122: ['_______ inflates its throat sac to amplify its electricity. By riding the wind, this Pokmon can fly over 430 miles in a day.', 'It uses its throat sac to store electricity generated by its wings. Theres hardly any oil in its feathers, so it is a poor swimmer.']
column1123: ['It always scowls in an attempt to make opponents take it seriously, but even crying children will burst into laughter when they see _______s face.', 'Its well-developed jaw and fangs are strong enough to crunch through boulders, and its thick fat makes for an excellent defense.']
column1124: ['This Pokmon can store energy in its large dewlap. _______ unleashes this energy all at once to blow away enemies.', '_______ loves playing with children. Though usually gentle, it takes on an intimidating look when protecting its family.']
column1125: ['Though usually a mellow Pokmon, it will sink its sharp, poison-soaked front teeth into any that anger it, causing paralysis in the object of its ire.', 'To keep enemies away from its territory, it paints markings around its nest using a poisonous liquid that has an acrid odor.']
column1126: ['The color of the poisonous saliva depends on what the Pokmon eats. _______ covers its fingers in its saliva and draws patterns on trees in forests.', 'Each _______ paints its own individual pattern, and it will paint that same pattern over and over again throughout its life.']
column1127: ['A soul unable to move on to the afterlife was blown around by the wind until it got tangled up with dried grass and became a Pokmon.', 'Not even _______ knows where it is headed as it tumbles across the wilderness, blown by the wind. It loathes getting wet.']
column1128: ['It will open the branches of its head to envelop its prey. Once it absorbs all the life energy it needs, it expels the prey and discards it.', '_______ wanders around arid regions. On rare occasions, mass outbreaks of these Pokmon will bury an entire town.']
column1129: ['_______ lives in muggy forests. The flaps that fall from its body are chewy and very delicious.', 'Though it looks like Tentacool, _______ is a completely different species. Its legs may be thin, but it can run at a speed of 30 mph.']
column1130: ['These Pokmon gather into groups and form colonies deep within forests. They absolutely hate it when strangers approach.', 'It coils its 10 tentacles around prey and sucks out their nutrients, causing the prey pain. The folds along the rim of its head are a popular delicacy.']
column1131: ['_______ hangs upside-down from cliffs, waiting for prey. But _______ cant remain in this position for long because its blood rushes to its head.', 'This Pokmon lives on sheer cliffs. It sidesteps opponents attacks, then lunges for their weak spots with its claws.']
column1132: ['The more sunlight this Pokmon bathes in, the more spicy chemicals are produced by its body, and thus the spicier its moves become.', 'Traditional Paldean dishes can be extremely spicy because they include the shed front teeth of _______ among their ingredients.']
column1133: ['The red head converts spicy chemicals into fire energy and blasts the surrounding area with a super spicy stream of flame.', 'The green head has turned vicious due to the spicy chemicals stimulating its brain. Once it goes on a rampage, there is no stopping it.']
column1134: ['This Pokmon creates a mud ball by mixing sand and dirt with psychic energy. It treasures its mud ball more than its own life.', 'It rolls its mud ball around while the energy it needs for evolution matures. Eventually the time comes for it to evolve.']
column1135: ['The body that supports the ball barely moves. Therefore, it is thought that the true body of this Pokmon is actually inside the ball.', 'An infant sleeps inside the ball. _______ rolls the ball soothingly with its legs to ensure the infant sleeps comfortably.']
column1136: ['_______s toes levitate about half an inch above the ground because of the psychic power emitted from the frills on the Pokmons belly.', 'It spends its time running around wastelands. If anyone steals its beloved berries, it will chase them down and exact its revenge.']
column1137: ['It immobilizes opponents by bathing them in psychic power from its large eyes. Despite its appearance, it has a vicious temperament.', 'It emits psychic power from the gaps between its multicolored frills and sprints at speeds greater than 120 mph.']
column1138: ['It swings its handmade hammer around to protect itself, but the hammer is often stolen by Pokmon that eat metal.', 'This Pokmon pounds iron scraps together to make a hammer. It will remake the hammer again and again until its satisfied with the result.']
column1139: ['This Pokmon will attack groups of Pawniard and Bisharp, gathering metal from them in order to create a large and sturdy hammer.', 'These Pokmon make their homes in piles of scrap metal. They test the strength of each others hammers by smashing them together.']
column1140: ['This intelligent Pokmon has a very daring disposition. It knocks rocks into the sky with its hammer, aiming for flying Corviknight.', 'The hammer tops 220 pounds, yet it gets swung around easily by _______ as it steals whatever it pleases and carries its plunder back home.']
column1141: ['This Pokmon can pick up the scent of a Veluza just over 65 feet away and will hide itself in the sand.', 'Though it looks like Diglett, _______ is an entirely different species. The resemblance seems to be a coincidental result of environmental adaptation.']
column1142: ['It has a vicious temperament, contrary to what its appearance may suggest. It wraps its long bodies around prey, then drags the prey into its den.', 'A variety of fish Pokmon, _______ was once considered to be a regional form of Dugtrio.']
column1143: ['It gathers things up in an apron made from shed feathers added to the Pokmons chest feathers, then drops those things from high places for fun.', '_______ uses the apron on its chest to bundle up food, which it carries back to its nest. It enjoys dropping things that make loud noises.']
column1144: ['It likes playing with others of its kind using the water ring on its tail. It uses ultrasonic waves to sense the emotions of other living creatures.', 'Its water ring is made from seawater mixed with a sticky fluid that _______ secretes from its blowhole.']
column1145: ['This Pokmon changes its appearance if it hears its allies calling for help. Palafin will never show anybody its moment of transformation.', 'Its physical capabilities are no different than a Finizens, but when its allies are in danger, it transforms and powers itself up.']
column1146: ['This Pokmon changes its appearance if it hears its allies calling for help. Palafin will never show anybody its moment of transformation.', 'Its physical capabilities are no different than a Finizens, but when its allies are in danger, it transforms and powers itself up.']
column1147: ['It is said that this Pokmon was born when an unknown poison Pokmon entered and inspirited an engine left at a scrap-processing factory.', 'The steel section is _______s actual body. This Pokmon clings to rocks and converts the minerals within into energy to fuel its activities.']
column1149: ['Apparently _______ has been allowing people to ride on its back since ancient times. Depictions of this have been found in 10,000-year-old murals.', 'It can sprint at over 70 mph while carrying a human. The riders body heat warms _______s back and lifts the Pokmons spirit.']
column1151: ['It absorbs nutrients from cave walls. The petals it wears are made of crystallized poison.', '_______s toxic mineral crystals look just like flower petals. This Pokmon scatters poisonous powder like pollen to protect itself.']
column1152: ['When this Pokmon detects danger, it will open up its crystalline petals and fire beams from its conical body.', '_______s petals are made of crystallized poison energy. It has recently become evident that these petals resemble Tera Jewels.']
column1155: ['This Pokmon apparently ties the base of its neck into a knot so that energy stored in its belly does not escape from its beak.', 'Thanks to a behavior of theirs known as synchronizing, an entire flock of these Pokmon can attack simultaneously in perfect harmony.']
column1156: ['This species left the ocean and began living on land a very long time ago. It seems to be closely related to Wailmer.', 'It lives in frigid regions in pods of five or so individuals. It loves the minerals found in snow and ice.']
column1157: ['This Pokmon wanders around snowy, icy areas. It protects its body with powerful muscles and a thick layer of fat under its skin.', 'Ice energy builds up in the horn on its upper jaw, causing the horn to reach cryogenic temperatures that freeze its surroundings.']
column1158: ['When _______ discards unnecessary flesh, its mind becomes honed and its psychic power increases. The spare flesh has a mild but delicious flavor.', '_______ has excellent regenerative capabilities. It sheds spare flesh from its body to boost its agility, then charges at its prey.']
column1159: ['This Pokmon is a glutton, but its bad at getting food. It teams up with a Tatsugiri to catch prey.', 'It treats Tatsugiri like its boss and follows it loyally. Though powerful, _______ is apparently not very smart.']
column1160: ['This species differing colors and patterns are apparently the result of Tatsugiri changing itself to suit the preferences of the prey it lures in.', 'This Pokmon tricks its opponents by playing dead. It is small and weak, but it uses its smarts to survive.']
column1161: ['This species differing colors and patterns are apparently the result of Tatsugiri changing itself to suit the preferences of the prey it lures in.', 'This Pokmon tricks its opponents by playing dead. It is small and weak, but it uses its smarts to survive.']
column1162: ['This species differing colors and patterns are apparently the result of Tatsugiri changing itself to suit the preferences of the prey it lures in.', 'This Pokmon tricks its opponents by playing dead. It is small and weak, but it uses its smarts to survive.']
column1163: ['When its anger rose beyond a critical point, this Pokmon gained power that is unfettered by the limits of its physical body.', 'It imbues its fists with the power of the rage that it kept hidden in its heart. Opponents struck by these imbued fists will be shattered to their core.']
column1164: ['When attacked, this Pokmon will retaliate by sticking thick spines out from its body. Its a risky move that puts everything on the line.', 'It lives at the bottom of ponds and swamps. It will carry Wooper on its back and ferry them across water from one shore to the other.']
column1165: ['Now that the brain waves from the head and tail are synced up, the psychic power of this Pokmon is 10 times stronger than Girafarigs.', 'The hardened head from the tail protects the head of the main body as _______ whips its long neck around to headbutt enemies.']
column1166: ['This Pokmon uses its hard tail to make its nest by boring holes into bedrock deep underground. The nest can reach lengths of over six miles.', 'It drives enemies out of its nest by sucking in enough air to fill its long, narrow lungs, then releasing the air in an intense blast.']
column1167: ['This Pokmon uses its hard tail to make its nest by boring holes into bedrock deep underground. The nest can reach lengths of over six miles.', 'It drives enemies out of its nest by sucking in enough air to fill its long, narrow lungs, then releasing the air in an intense blast.']
column1168: ['Only a Bisharp that stands above all others in its vast army can evolve into _______.', 'Though it commands a massive army in battle, its not skilled at devising complex strategies. It just uses brute strength to keep pushing.']
column1169: ['Sightings of this Pokmon have occurred in recent years. The name _______ was taken from a creature listed in a certain book.', 'This creature resembles a mysterious Pokmon that, according to a paranormal magazine, has lived since ancient times.']
column1170: ['There has been only one reported sighting of this Pokmon. It resembles a mysterious creature depicted in an old expedition journal.', 'It resembles a mysterious Pokmon described in a paranormal magazine as a Jigglypuff from one billion years ago.']
column1171: ['It is possible that the creature listed as _______ in a certain book could actually be this Pokmon.', 'It bears a slight resemblance to a Pokmon described in a dubious magazine as a cross between a dinosaur and a mushroom.']
column1172: ['This Pokmon has characteristics similar to those of _______, a creature mentioned in a certain book.', 'It has similar features to a ghostly pterosaur that was covered in a paranormal magazine, but the two have little else in common.']
column1173: ['This mysterious Pokmon has some similarities to a creature that an old book introduced as _______.', 'This Pokmon somewhat resembles an ancient form of Volcarona that was introduced in a dubious magazine.']
column1174: ['No records exist of this Pokmon being caught. Data is lacking, but the Pokmons traits match up with a creature shown in an expedition journal.', 'It slightly resembles a Magneton that lived for 10,000 years and was featured in an article in a paranormal magazine.']
column1175: ['This Pokmon closely resembles a scientific weapon that a paranormal magazine claimed was sent to this planet by aliens.', 'Sightings of this Pokmon have occurred in recent years. It resembles a mysterious object described in an old expedition journal.']
column1176: ['Its shape is similar to a robot featured in a paranormal magazine article. The robot was said to have been created by an ancient civilization.', 'It resembles a mysterious object mentioned in an old book. There are only two reported sightings of this Pokmon.']
column1177: ['It is very similar to a cyborg covered exclusively by a paranormal magazine. The cyborg was said to be the modified form of a certain athlete.', 'This Pokmon shares many similarities with _______, an object mentioned in a certain expedition journal.']
column1178: ['It resembles a certain Pokmon introduced in a paranormal magazine, described as the offspring of a Hydreigon that fell in love with a robot.', 'Its possible that _______, an object described in an old book, may actually be this Pokmon.']
column1179: ['This Pokmon resembles an unknown object described in a paranormal magazine as a UFO sent to observe humanity.', 'No records exist of this species being caught. Data is lacking, but the Pokmons traits match up with an object described in an old book.']
column1180: ['It has some similarities to a Pokmon introduced in a dubious magazine as a Tyranitar from one billion years into the future.', 'Some of its notable features match those of an object named within a certain expedition journal as _______.']
column1181: ['_______ absorbs heat through its dorsal fin and converts the heat into ice energy. The higher the temperature, the more energy _______ stores.', 'This Pokmon lives in forests and craggy areas. Using the power of its dorsal fin, it cools the inside of its nest like a refrigerator.']
column1182: ['_______ freezes the air around it, protecting its face with an ice mask and turning its dorsal fin into a blade of ice.', 'It attacks with the blade of its frozen dorsal fin by doing a front flip in the air. _______s strong back and legs allow it to pull off this technique.']
column1183: ['This Pokmon blasts cryogenic air out from its mouth. This air can instantly freeze even liquid-hot lava.', 'It launches itself into battle by flipping upside down and spewing frigid air from its mouth. It finishes opponents off with its dorsal blade.']
column1184: ['This Pokmon was born inside a treasure chest about 1,500 years ago. It sucks the life-force out of scoundrels who try to steal the treasure.', 'It lives inside an old treasure chest. Sometimes it gets left in shop corners since no one realizes its actually a Pokmon.']
column1185: ['This Pokmon was born inside a treasure chest about 1,500 years ago. It sucks the life-force out of scoundrels who try to steal the treasure.', 'It lives inside an old treasure chest. Sometimes it gets left in shop corners since no one realizes its actually a Pokmon.']
column1186: ['Its body seems to be made up of 1,000 coins. This Pokmon gets along well with others and is quick to make friends with anybody.', 'It has a sturdy body made up of stacked coins. _______ overwhelms its enemies by firing coin after coin at them in quick succession.']
column1187: ['The grudge of a person punished for writing the kings evil deeds upon wooden tablets has clad itself in dead leaves to become a Pokmon.', 'It drains the life-force from vegetation, causing nearby forests to instantly wither and fields to turn barren.']
column1188: ['This Pokmon can control 100 tons of fallen snow. It plays around innocently by leaping in and out of avalanches it has caused.', 'The hatred of those who perished by the sword long ago has clad itself in snow and become a Pokmon.']
column1189: ['The fear poured into an ancient ritual vessel has clad itself in rocks and dirt to become a Pokmon.', 'It slowly brings its exceedingly heavy head down upon the ground, splitting the earth open with huge fissures that run over 160 feet deep.']
column1190: ['It controls flames burning at over 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit. It casually swims through the sea of lava it creates by melting rock and sand.', 'The envy accumulated within curved beads that sparked multiple conflicts has clad itself in fire and become a Pokmon.']
column1191: ['It is possible that this is the creature listed as _______ in an expedition journal that still holds many mysteries.', 'According to an article in a dubious magazine, this Pokmon has some connection to a phenomenon that occurs in a certain region.']
column1192: ['It has some similarities to a mad scientists invention covered in a paranormal magazine.', 'Its possible that this is the object listed as _______ in a certain expedition journal.']
column1193: ['This seems to be the Winged King mentioned in an old expedition journal. It was said to have split the land with its bare fists.', 'This Pokmon resembles Cyclizar, but it is far burlier and more ferocious. Nothing is known about its ecology or other features.']
column1194: ['Much remains unknown about this creature. It resembles Cyclizar, but it is far more ruthless and powerful.', 'This seems to be the Iron Serpent mentioned in an old book. The Iron Serpent is said to have turned the land to ash with its lightning.']
